test connectivity between two servers 
we have server a  and server b  and need to test connectivity port 80  is it  open or  not 

1. Using telnet (if installed)
telnet <server_b_ip> 80

2. Using nc (Netcat)
nc -zv <server_b_ip> 80

3. Using nmap (Port scanning)
nmap -p 80 <server_b_ip>

4-Create a Dummy HTTP Service pythion 
sudo python3 -m http.server 80
